msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/color_management_settings.rst:162
msgid "Rec 709 Linear"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/color_management_settings.rst:165
msgid "This is an HDR color space as defined by Rec. 2100 specification. This is the only color space in which Krita can pass HDR data to the compositor!"
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/color_management_settings.rst:170
msgid "In the current implementation of HDR conversions in Krita, the *diffuse white* of this HDR color space is always fixed to 80 cd/m². In other words, if you take an image in a scene-referred linear space (e.g. ACEScg), convert it into Rec 2020 PQ, then RGB color value ``(1.0, 1.0, 1.0)`` of this image will be mapped to 80 cd/m² value in the PQ-range."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/color_management_settings.rst:176
msgid "When Krita passes \"Rec 2020 PQ\"-data to the compositor, it correctly declares this *diffuse white* point to the compositor. The compositor, in turn, applies an additional curve to the image to adapt this level to the \"SDR brightness level\" selected by the user in the system-wide HDR configuration page."
msgstr ""

#: ../../reference_manual/preferences/color_management_settings.rst:179
msgid "Rec 2020 PQ"
msgstr ""

